casebody.data:
No. 63,

Misc.

Ex parte Denver & Rio Grande Western Railroad Company Committees and Trustees. December 16, 1946. Walter J. Cummings, Jr. for petitioners. Acting Solicitor General Washington, John D. Goodloe and W. Meade Fletcher filed a memorandum for the Reconstruction Finance Corporation.

The motion for leave to file petition for writs of mandamus and prohibition is denied.
